title: Print, "Dedicatory page of the set "Mediceae familiae rerum feliciter gestarum Victoria et triumphi"", 1578
provenance: Giovanni Piancastelli: Mrs. Edward D. Brandegee
dimensions:
Sheet: 30.9 x 41.9 cm (12 3/16 x 16 1/2 in.)
Printing block: 21.1 x 30.8 cm (8 5/16 x 12 1/8 in.)
creditline: Museum purchase through gift of various donors and from Eleanor G. Hewitt Fund
description: Vertical rectangle.  An escutcheon surrounded by many animals, statues of Diana and another huntress, two hunters and the coat of arms of the Medici with spears and  horns, contains the text beginning: "COSMVS MED. MAGN: ETRVRIAE" and ending with : "Johannes Stradensis Flanfrius inuen.  Philippus Galle Sculp. et exud:/1578."  Bottom center: Ad Lectorem.  Framing lines, bottom: Exornant aulasque aulea parentis Hetrusci, Pluribid exemplis his tibi lector habe."
